docs.lead_paragraph: The U.S. Chamber of Commerce on Friday called on the government to ratchet up pressure on India over intellectual property rights, in a move that could help prevent Indian companies from producing cheap generic versions of medicines still under patent protection.

docs.lead_paragraph: Dr. Thomas R. Insel’s twisted path to his role as director of the National Institute of Mental Health is a tour of where psychiatric science has been, where it’s going and why.
docs.abstract: Profile of Dr Thomas R Insel, brain scientist who runs the National Institute of Mental Health; Insel's twisting path to position traces development of psychiatric science; his tenure spans nearly half century and coincides with contentious top-down overhaul of field.
